          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The counter wall was covered with 1.0 g/cm2 of lead.",
                "When the Ra-Be was introduced into the large lead",
                "block counts increased. With the 200 mc Ra-Be source",
                "in the lead block additional lead (in plates 15x30",
                "cm2) was placed behind the counter and produced a",
                "further increase in the count. The increases in",
                "counts vs. Pb thickness establish the existence of a",
                "gamma-ray produced by the action of fast neutrons on",
                "lead and the magnitude of its self-absorption",
                "indicates an energy somewhat less than 1 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Compiler's comment: It could be levels in 204,206,",
                "207Pb below 1 MeV. Ra-Be neutron spectrum is below 13",
                "MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
